<TITLE> Govt approves 2 new power stations </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, October 2 (bdnews24.com)  The government gave the go-ahead Tuesday for two new private power stations in Sylhet and Habiganj districts, an adviser said. Corrected The cabinet committee on public purchase approved the power plants that will have a total capacity of 90 MW, finance and commerce adviser Mirza Azizul Islam told reporters. An 80 MW power station will be built at Shahjibazaar in Habiganj and will be operated by Youth Spinning Mill. Another 10 MW unit will be set up at Kumargaon in Sylhet City, which will be operated by Desh Energy Ltd. "The government will buy electricity from the Shahjibazaar plant at the rate of Tk 2.26 per unit," the adviser said. "As for the Kumargaon station the rate will be Tk 2.36 per unit. These rates will apply for 15 years after they start generating power," added Azizul. Also present at the meeting were law and information adviser Mainul Hosein, power adviser Tapan Chowdhury and health adviser Matiur Rahman. bdnews24
